[Marjorie Pollack was kind enough to provide this translation from the
original. As to whether treatment has been successful or there is some
other answer remains to be shown. Various hospitals have claimed high
success rates but the data are unclear. For example, the etiologic agent
of hantavirus pulmonary syndrome in Uruguay may be a hantavirus with low
human pathogenicity or the vertebrate host, the rodent carrying the virus,
may not excrete enough virus to provide an infected human with a fatal
dose. - Mod.CHC
